rgy companies are major foreign winners from Washington’s landmark climate law as they benefit from tax credits and a turn away from China. Hanwha Solutions Corp., a solar equipment maker with manufacturing and research sites in North America, said it’s expecting to get more than $200 million in tax credits annually from next year. Photographer: SeongJoon Cho&amp;amp;#x2F;Bloomberg" width="580"/&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;&lt;div style="display:none"&gt;&lt;![endif]--&gt;&lt;img alt="2022 年 10 月 12 日星期三，韩国忠清北道镇川市韩华解决方案公司 Q Cells 部门工厂的生产线正在生产太阳能电池板。韩国清洁能源公司是华盛顿具有里程碑意义的气候法的主要外国赢家，因为它们受益于税收抵免和远离中国。韩华解决方案公司是一家在北美设有制造和研究基地的太阳能设备制造商，该公司表示，预计从明年起每年将获得超过 2 亿美元的税收抵免。摄影师：SeongJoon Cho&amp;amp;#x2F;Bloomberg" src="https://assets.bwbx.io/images/users/iqjWHBFdfxIU/iEpworvSBh2M/v11/-1x-1.jpg" style="width: 100%; display: block; margin-bottom: 4px;" /&gt;&lt;!--[if mso]&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;![endif]--&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;figcaption&gt;&lt;div style="font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.4;"&gt;中国的太阳能电池板制造&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;div style="font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.4; font-style: italic;"&gt;摄影师：SeongJoon Cho/彭博社&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;p style="margin-top: 24px; font-size: 16px;"&gt;这一预测形成了一幅复杂的图景。智&lt;a href="https://links.message.bloomberg.com/a/sc/FEGy2aV8xbyi9z6vDYqG0AmquwN6gJLp9rhSAINEj8RuippmBFxxOOA0CicT_0zN3s79fkrtEmA57Zux5hwvmymWE3780XTS4qpvlfNt2toZishT-O49Cqzn4tbNWwXqZQSSvt8VK1L3pEW9i5NGY1I0lUIxUT8ik99oS0xxfXCsTGqhbJBCd0oodbILqnMiRrqu-H-X2D1Jqf_Afk9_-B4XZgN1zUZYX98yodEa1ERztAsA46AE2tiEnxOpMiJaks2cSx8TPq_EkPxH4zQYPNl6KBCUBydWNMy7fkor6b8AUJEg0sYAtafUEnds2peJ0yGW9Qnd6jU8Ef3ipkbaW9Px4XG5IHR5efiRV2FIsbsDxk7BsKCkCsVarqPNwjfyyqkk85gOFDfatQ1m5LyxNWj_NxvJMy1KS5-LRIzZa8KkrWOzNln1d3t7iWx4gJu2_Ps/et9Qptt1bNYrZcKFVDljMsi4xAsAX-mF/19" rel="noopener noreferrer" style="font-size: inherit; color: #00e;" target="_blank" title="勃鲁盖尔AISBL"&gt;库布鲁盖尔&lt;/a&gt;表示，中国对伊朗石油进口的依赖将对其能源战略构成“ &lt;a href="https://links.message.bloomberg.com/s/c/wUeKCW32wuz_2HIYb38z3i2ANuQV5bbe_x